         <p>The records are arranged chronologically.</p>
      </arrangement>
      <bioghist id="aspace_4e5fe98f27ecd64a0feb1901b1836777">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Established in 1987, the Lesbian and Gay Studies Center at Yale promoted, organized, and desseminated research on the lives and history of lesbians and gay men through conferences, lectures, and a newsletter. The center was founded by Yale faculty and students, but was not administered by Yale University.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_f7fc0b4fb46e7e02951f3c3595fdce2e">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of meeting minutes, correspondence, newsletters, an annual report, and conference brochures documenting the establishment and activities of the Lesbian and Gay Studies Center at Yale. Also included is a compilation of newscasts (VHS) concerning the protests following the arrest of some participants of the 1989 conference, Inside/Out, sponsered by the center.</p>
      </scopecontent>
